There are a few places that you visit that’d leave an impression on you like Italy. Italy offerings range from History, art, food, music, architecture, culture to beautiful scenery. Here are some of the must-visit places: <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-834678 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Juliets-house-in-Vernice.-Photo-deliciouslydirectionless.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="450" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Juliets-house-in-Vernice.-Photo-deliciouslydirectionless.jpg 800w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Juliets-house-in-Vernice.-Photo-deliciouslydirectionless-640x360.jpg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Juliets-house-in-Vernice.-Photo-deliciouslydirectionless-320x180.jpg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Juliets-house-in-Vernice.-Photo-deliciouslydirectionless-281x158.jpg 281w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Juliets-house-in-Vernice.-Photo-deliciouslydirectionless-562x316.jpg 562w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Juliets-house-in-Vernice.-Photo-deliciouslydirectionless-531x299.jpg 531w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Juliets-house-in-Vernice.-Photo-deliciouslydirectionless-1062x598.jpg 1062w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Juliets-house-in-Vernice.-Photo-deliciouslydirectionless-487x274.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Juliets-house-in-Vernice.-Photo-deliciouslydirectionless-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /> Get lost in the pleasures of Venice, one of the most populous and visited cities in the country. What other city provides you with water lined up on the road beside houses and boats serving as buses? La Casa di Giulietta is one of the highlights in Verona. This is because it is the home of the fictional character of Shakespeare’s Juliet. However, one of the reasons why this house is a favourite of tourists is that the tale is true. The fictional character belonged to the dell’Capello of the Capuletti family while the Romeo belonged to the Montecchi family. So if you are looking for the real things, this is it. Get enchanted in Lake Como, Italy’s most beautiful lake and the third largest lake in Italy. The lake takes the shape of the letter Y cutting across. A favourite spot for the rich and famous since the ancient Roman times. At Lake Como, tourists are enjoined to sail, windsurf and take in the stunning landscape while indulging in spas. One mention of Italy’s capital, Rome and it brings back a lot of memories. Rome is one of the most unique places in the world that has some of its present places. Some of the glorious places that tourists can have a feel of are the Colosseum, the Forum, the Pantheon, the Appian Way, the Vatican and the Palatine Hill. Florence is the home of the Renaissance. Get in tune with some of the exotic arts and architecture.